Subject:
Question about Regular Sync
Description:
Dear Support Team,

I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to ask you a question about the Regular Sync feature of the Salesforce and Xero integration.

According to the documentation, the Regular Sync is scheduled every 13 minutes and fetches the data from Xero that were modified within the scheduled 28-minute time period. It also performs the auto-match for Xero contacts, associates invoices with opportunities or orders, updates account and opportunity rollups, and marks records as archived in Salesforce if they are archived in Xero.

My question is: How can I change the frequency and the time period of the Regular Sync? I would like to sync my data more often and with a shorter time interval.

I appreciate your time and attention. Thank you for your help.

Sincerely, 
Jones
Technosoft

I have checked the Invoice Auto Mapping settings and they are correct. I have also checked the data in both systems and they are consistent. I have tried to manually sync the data, but the issue persists.

Subject:
Feedback on Regular Sync
Description:
Dear Support Team,

I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to give you some feedback on the Regular Sync feature of the Salesforce and Xero integration.

I have been using the Regular Sync feature for a few weeks and I am very impressed with its performance and functionality. It has saved me a lot of time and effort by syncing my data between Salesforce and Xero automatically and accurately. It has also improved my visibility and reporting by updating the account and opportunity rollups and marking the records as archived in Salesforce if they are archived in Xero.

I especially like the auto-match feature, which matches my contacts in Xero with my accounts in Salesforce based on the criteria that I have set up. This has eliminated the need for manual matching and ensured that my data is consistent and up-to-date.

I want to thank you for developing and providing this feature. It has made my work easier and more efficient. I look forward to using more features of the Salesforce and Xero integration in the future.

Sincerely, 
Jackob
Sharklite
